spandsp
=======

spandsp is a free software collection of telephony signal processing
DSP routines, originally developed by Steve Underwood and now
maintained at https://github.com/freeswitch/spandsp.

Earlier development phases of synthmodem vendored spandsp directly
as compiled native addons (`src/native/`). That tree was removed in
cleanup-phase-2; no spandsp C/C++ source is shipped today. However,
several of synthmodem's pure-JavaScript DSP modules contain code
that was ported from spandsp source — algorithms, state machines,
filter coefficient tables, and named constants reimplemented in
JavaScript with documented adaptations. Those JS modules are
therefore derivative works of spandsp.

Upstream project:  https://github.com/freeswitch/spandsp
Original author:   Steve Underwood <steveu@coppice.org>
Upstream copyright: Copyright (C) 2003-2009 Steve Underwood

Files containing ported code
----------------------------

The following synthmodem source files contain code derived from
spandsp. Each file's header records the specific upstream source
file(s) used as the basis for the port and what was preserved,
adapted, or omitted relative to upstream.

  * src/dsp/V8Sequencer.js
      Faithful port of spandsp's `src/v8.c` — the V.8 negotiation
      sample-accurate state machine.

  * src/dsp/protocols/V22Demodulator.js
      Faithful port of spandsp's `src/v22bis_rx.c` — the V.22 / V.22bis
      receive pipeline, including the bandpass-RRC filter, AGC, Costas
      carrier tracking, T/2 LMS equalizer, Gardner symbol-sync
      detector, and the RX training state machine. Includes inline
      citations to specific upstream line numbers throughout.

  * src/dsp/protocols/V22RxRRC.js
      Direct port of the bandpass-RRC filter coefficient tables from
      spandsp's `src/v22bis_rx_1200_rrc.h` and
      `src/v22bis_rx_2400_rrc.h`. Numeric values verbatim.

  * src/dsp/protocols/V22Common.js
      The `V22Scrambler` class is a direct port of spandsp's
      `scramble()` / `descramble()` functions from `src/v22bis_tx.c`
      and `src/v22bis_rx.c`. The remainder of this file
      (constants, pulse-shape helper) is independently authored
      from the V.22bis specification.

  * src/dsp/protocols/V22.js
      The V.22bis modulator and answerer-side handshake state machine
      are modelled after spandsp's `src/v22bis_tx.c` (and reference
      `src/v22bis_rx.c` for the cross-side state transitions).
      Several specific design choices, named constants, and per-line
      formula references are taken from upstream and cited inline.
      (synthmodem's S1 detection uses an independently-developed
      spectral test in place of spandsp's symbol-stream-based
      detector; that variation is documented in the file header.)

  * src/dsp/protocols/FskCommon.js
      The `CoherentFskDemodulator` class is a faithful port of
      spandsp's `src/fsk.c` receive logic (quadrature DDS correlators,
      sliding dot-product matched filter, central-bit-stability UART
      framing). The `FskModulator` class implements spandsp's
      fractional-baud accumulator approach (`src/fsk.c` `fsk_tx`)
      with constants taken from spandsp's `preset_fsk_specs` for V.21,
      Bell 103, and V.23.

