Modifications from upstream
---------------------------

By their nature, the ports listed above are not byte-identical
copies of the spandsp source. The differences include:

  * Translation from C to JavaScript (with IEEE float arithmetic
    in place of spandsp's int16/fixed-point in some files; spandsp
    has a `SPANDSP_USE_FIXED_POINT` build switch and we follow the
    floating-point alternate path).
  * UART framing integrated into the demodulator classes
    (spandsp's consumers handle UART externally via a `put_bit`
    callback; our async data interface emits `Buffer` events).
  * Carrier-presence gating exposed as a constructor flag for
    A/B testing (spandsp uses an internal `signal_present` flag).
  * S1 detection in V.22bis replaced with a spectral test on the
    raw input audio (spandsp uses a symbol-stream-based detector;
    see V22.js header for the rationale).
  * V.22bis training state machine integrated with synthmodem's
    sample-accurate handshake driver in V22.js.

The per-file headers in each ported module document the
adaptations specific to that module in greater detail. These
headers, taken together with this notice, satisfy LGPL-2.1 §1's
requirement (now §1 of GPL-2.0 by virtue of the §3 election)
that modified files carry prominent notices stating that they
have been changed and the date of any change.

Corresponding source
--------------------

The synthmodem repository IS the corresponding source for the
JavaScript ports. The .js files listed above are themselves the
distributable source form — there is no separate compilation step
or bundled binary derived from them. GPL-2.0 §3(a) is satisfied by
publishing the synthmodem repository.

We do NOT vendor the spandsp upstream C source tree. That source
remains available from the upstream project at
https://github.com/freeswitch/spandsp. Vendoring the upstream is
not required for compliance: we do not ship any compiled spandsp
binary, and the obligation to provide corresponding source attaches
to what we distribute, not to the historical reference material
used during development. Recipients who wish to compare the ports
to the upstream may use the inline file/line references in each
ported module and fetch the corresponding spandsp source directly.
